<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>What is the natural rate of unemployment?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Zero unemployment in the economy</option>
            <option letter="b">The unemployment rate when the economy is at full employment</option>
            <option letter="c">The unemployment rate during recessions</option>
            <option letter="d">The highest unemployment rate in a business cycle</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The natural rate of unemployment is the unemployment rate when the economy is at full employment, consisting of frictional and structural unemployment but no cyclical unemployment.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>Which type of unemployment occurs when workers are temporarily between jobs?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Structural unemployment</option>
            <option letter="b">Cyclical unemployment</option>
            <option letter="c">Frictional unemployment</option>
            <option letter="d">Seasonal unemployment</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>Frictional unemployment occurs when workers are temporarily between jobs as they search for new employment or enter the workforce for the first time.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>The GDP deflator measures:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">The price level of all goods and services produced in an economy</option>
            <option letter="b">The price level of consumer goods only</option>
            <option letter="c">The cost of a fixed basket of consumer goods</option>
            <option letter="d">The inflation rate for imported goods</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The GDP deflator measures the overall price level of all goods and services produced within an economy, including consumer goods, capital goods, exports, and government services.</explanation>
    </question>

    <question>
        <prompt>Real interest rate is calculated by:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Adding inflation rate to nominal interest rate</option>
            <option letter="b">Multiplying nominal interest rate by inflation rate</option>
            <option letter="c">Subtracting inflation rate from nominal interest rate</option>
            <option letter="d">Dividing nominal interest rate by inflation rate</option>
        </options>
        <answer>c</answer>
        <explanation>The real interest rate is calculated by subtracting the inflation rate from the nominal interest rate. This shows the actual purchasing power gained from interest after accounting for inflation.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
